    • getSysId

      protected edu.wpi.first.wpilibj2.command.sysid.SysIdRoutine getSysId(edu.wpi.first.wpilibj2.command.SubsystemBase swerveSubsystem)
      Returns a SysIdRoutine instance configured for system identification of the drive.

      If the instance variable sysId is null, a new SysIdRoutine instance is created with the provided SubsystemBase and a default configuration. The default configuration includes a no-op mechanism and a logger which records the state of the SysIdRoutine to the Logger.

      Parameters:
      swerveSubsystem - The subsystem to add to the requirements of the SysIdRoutine
      Returns:
      A SysIdRoutine instance configured for system identification of the drive
